-- JPMorgan updates disclosures of legal risks
-- By David Henry in New York
-- Mon Aug 04, 2014 05:33PM EDT
-- None



NEW YORK, Aug 4 (Reuters) - JPMorgan Chase & Co <JPM.N> on Monday pegged its possible legal costs in excess of litigation reserves at $4.6 billion at the end of June, up from $4.5 billion at the end of March.

The company also disclosed that it is responding to questions from trustees offices of U.S. bankruptcy courts about notices on mortgage payment changes and escrow statements in bankruptcy proceedings. The disclosures came in a quarterly filing with the U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission. A JPMorgan spokesman declined to comment further on the bankruptcy trustee questions.